The Durban International Convention Centre is hosting Africa's Travel Indaba. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Tourism Minister Derek Hanekom says Africa's Travel Indaba has become more than just an industry meeting place. Travel delegates and the media from around the world have come together under one roof to find out what Africa has to offer. READ: Police seize counterfeit goods worth R28m The Durban International Convention Centre is hosting Africa's Travel Indaba and showcases Southern Africa’s best tourism products. More than 10, 000 delegates and 7, 000 exhibitors have attended the event. With 65 countries attending the Indaba, an estimated R40-million is expected to be spent.